args:
After dispatching the demonic entities, Nevin's
team pools their information with Harle, then
makes for Grams to report their discoveries.
Meanwhile, Regina asks her guard to deliver a
message to Origa and secures an audience.
That should be the last of the\ndemonic entities.
You felt it too, huh? These demonic entities\nare definitely different from the ones we\nscrapped with before.
Until now, they were being fed a supply of\nmiasma from the sealing stone, which is\nwhat made 'em such a pain.
I know I'm new to this particular party,\nbut if they're easier to deal with now,\nisn't that a good thing?
Sorry, but who are you again?
Ah, where ARE my manners? Harle.\nThe pleasure is all mine.
Prince {player_name} spoke of a\nHarle once—something about a smirking\nchief of the Capital Guard.

Well, I happen to think I have a lovely
smile, but that's neither here nor there.
While your friend was talking about me,
he wasn't actually talking about...ME.
Would you like to explain that, or should\nI just stand here and blink at you?
For some years—until very recently—\nI was trapped in another world.
Worse yet, an impostor stole my face and\ngot up to all manner of mischief in the\nmeantime. It's all been quite the bother.
I heard you say something about that to\nBasileus earlier, but...
Mmm? Something the matter? I can't help\nbut notice that accusatory stare of yours.\nHeaven forfend that you doubt me!
Actually, I very much do—and I intend to\nexercise extreme caution around you given\nwhat {player_name} said.
A prudent, if not painfully stinging, rebuke.\nAnd a shame, as I was hoping we might\nall enjoy a lovely partnership.
Wait, you want to work with us? Do you\neven know what it is we're doing?
Stopping Satan's revival. I mean, duh.

As it turns out, I've been conducting
something of a solo investigation and
came here as part of that. It's much the
same for you, I imagine?
People usually bring something to the\ntable when they mean to cooperate.
And I have just oodles of things for you,\nwhich is why it breaks my poor little heart\nto hear you don't trust me.

The most revelatory information in the
world isn't worth a mound of bear dung
if you don't trust the source, so I suppose
I'll just stop wasting your time.
It's like he WANTS me to punch him...
Fine, then. Let's all just pretend we trust\neach other and pool what info we have.
You're really going to hand over everything\nwe know to this boor, Nevin?

We saw for ourselves that he and Basileus
aren't together, so the enemy of my enemy
is my blah blah blah whatever. Might as
well share what we know.
(Especially since I plan to keep the\nsensitive bits to myself...)
I certainly have no objections on my end.\nBut rather than pooling, I propose a trade.

The slightest of distinctions, I admit, but
I'm simply attempting to ensure a format
most conducive to mutual aid, seeing as
I AM the untrusted party here.
(For all his whining about trust, he clearly\ndoesn't have faith in us either.)
(Though I suppose that helps to solidify\nthe fact he's not plotting something.)
Fine, but not here. Let's head somewhere\na bit more private, then we can trade or\nswap or whatever to your heart's content.
Ack, it's so bright! When the sun comes\nup here, it doesn't mess around.
You okay, Pi? If you're sleepy, you can rest\nyour head in Mama's lap.
I'm quite awake, thank you. Besides,\nthis is no time for sleeping.
How you feeling there, Ramiel?\nPower coming back yet?
Still not good. It's extremely unstable.\nRight now, I can't even communicate\nwith Sandalphon.
Which means we'll have to return to\nGrams and deliver our report in person.

So you learned about the fragments of
Satan held by the Five Archdemons,
as well as the vessel that binds and
animates them?
Well, that IS a tasty bit of intel.
Your turn now. And it better be good.
Then let's see how this little tidbit\nstrikes you...
The five fragments necessary to bring \nSatan back are already in my impostor's\npossession.
It seems that one was news to you!\nAnd yes, dear miss, I am sure;\nI confirmed it while tracking him.
I can't speak for what he's done since\nleaving to join the Five Archdemons,\nbut at least we've managed a fair trade.

(I was gonna tell him we already knew
that and press him for more intel, but
thanks to Pinon and her big, honest
mouth, that's off the table.)
Sounds like we're really up against it here.
(Rrrgh! I wanna slap the smug grin off this\nguy's face! If they've got the fragments and\nthe vessel, there's nothing... No. Wait.)
Are you referring to that cryptic note in the\njournal? The one about more testing being\nrequired?
The journal mentioned the soul?\nNow that IS surprising.
Well, then, a little bonus tip because\nwe're such good friends...

The fragments and vessel are insufficient
to revive Satan. They need his soul—his
mana—which is sealed away deep within
another world.
So even restoring his flesh and blood isn't\na true resurrection without the soul?
Precisely. I also learned that while digging\ninto my impostor's movements.
Until very recently, he was hard at work\nsearching for the key that would allow him\nto retrieve that soul from the other world.
I was unable to get inside to see it myself,\nbut I'm given to understand it is a Sacred\nShard infused with Metatron's mana.
Interesting. And this key is in the\npossession of your impostor?
Indeed. Though it isn't quite checkmate\njust yet, for using the key entails a rather\nlarge-scale ritual.
If the clues left behind by my impostor are\nto be believed, it requires a mass human\nsacrifice with 666 victims.
They're going to butcher that many people\nas part of some....some RITUAL?!
The fact such extreme measures are\nrequired is an indication of just how\npowerful Satan's soul truly is.
And how do they plan on rounding up\nthese 666 unfortunates?
I think I know just the event...
Grams will be flooded with people from\nthe Northern Church—more than enough\nto complete this grim task.
But the Auspecalia is only days away!\nWe have to warn them!
Easy there, Pinon. Think for a second.\nWho exactly are you planning to warn?
Everyone traveling to Grams who is\nabout to be SLAUGHTERED, Nevin!

And considering the schedule, most of
them are already in Grams by now.
Warning them won't help—we need to
shut the festival down.
Ramiel? Any progress on reaching\nour buddy Sandalphon?
No. The effects of Basileus's device persist.
It is the same with me.
(Basileus knew this would happen.\nBut we have to do something...)
We're going to Grams. I assume you're\ncoming with us, Harle?
I wouldn't miss it for the world. After all,\nthe ones who humiliated me will be\nwaiting there. Heh heh heh...
Then let's move out. Everyone ready?
Hold up, honey bun! You've got a patch of\nhair in the back that's standing up funny.\nLet Mama fix that for you.
I can't wait to repay the favor to those who\ncrossed me. Oh, but they will pay...
And what do you want me to do?
We've been at this long enough for me\nto know how you think.
I need you to run a little errand for me...
Curia of the Ilian Church of Grams\nHolding Cells
Can't believe I'm stuck on guard duty today\nof all days. I'm gonna miss my daughter's\nfirst Auspecalia!
The Day of the Auspecalia Festival...
This is all your fault, you know! What kind\nof madwoman kills a priest and then sets\nan entire town on fire, huh?
A little late to be playing the innocent.\nEverybody knows about your plot to\ndestroy the Church.
I just feel sorry for poor Archbishop Basel.\nHe's under house arrest because he didn't\nsee his subordinates' betrayal coming.
Imagine a good, honest man like him\nbeing blamed for you traitorous curs.\nShameless, the lot of you.
No remorse at all, eh? You could stand to\nlearn a thing or two from the guy we\nbrought in with you.
Hasn't said boo since he got here.\nInstead, he's spent his time reflecting\non his crimes.
You there. Guard. Put me through to the\nAus...er, to Her Holiness the Pope.\nI must speak with her about a matter.
She will listen if you give her the name\n＂Alphir.＂ If you value your life and the lives\nof your loved ones, you will do this thing.
Pffft! You think I'm going to fall for an\nobvious bluff like that?
If you think it a bluff, then by all means,\ndo nothing. Just don't blame me when\ntragedy befalls your household.
...Fine! But just a message, and only once.\nWaste of time anyway—there's no way\nHer Holiness will listen to some heretic.
I don't mean to doubt you, Regina, but\nwhy would Origa give us the time of day?
Because I'm betting she hasn't forgotten.
More importantly, Ryszarda, what of your\nSigil connection to Rafael?
Nothing. I can't feel a thing—and I don't\nknow if this is something that'll get better\non its own or not.
So you're in the same position we are.\nSadly, we can't hope to break out of here\nby force without the Sigil's strength.
Which means we're left counting on Faris\nand his plotting. Uriel didn't say anything\nwhen you were captured, did he?
No. Well, other than he was sure Faris\nwould get passing marks.
Ever the doting father. Still, if they already\nhad a plan in mind then, it would be to...\nYes, of course!
But in that case, I'd want a fallback—\nor ideally two.
I don't know what the hell is going on\nhere, but...Regina, Her Holiness is asking\nfor you!
Grams\nCuria of the Ilian Church of Grams
You mustn't, Your Holiness! That woman\ncommands the apostles, which makes her\nchief among traitors!
I will not repeat myself, Cardinal.\nNow stand down.
...Understood, Your Holiness. But do not\nhesitate to call for me if anything\nuntoward happens.
That nuisance has been sent packing.\nIf you've something to say to me,\nnow is the time.
I'd hoped we could meet again under\nbetter circumstances, but I'm glad to see\nyou looking well regardless.
Then I'll be blunt: These accusations of\nbetrayal are nothing but lies, and I request\nour immediate release.
Denied. I won't retract an order once given.

Add whatever conditions you must.
Have us monitored if that helps.
I only ask that you allow us to investigate
this matter and clear our names.
Denied. You can wait in your cell until the\nAuspecalia is over. ...Was that all?
Nope! I have a mountain of things to talk\nabout, and I assume you feel the same\nsince you agreed to see me.
I hoped we might have a proper talk\nbefore I attended to my duties at the\nAuspecalia...Sister.
